  1. SOC estimation of cell with Kalman Filter[code]:
  • A more accurate battery state of charge estimation method for electric vehicles is developed based on a nonlinear cell model and an Extended Kalman Filter supported by open source experimental data
  • A nonlinear cell model is constructed by separating the model into a nonlinear open circuit voltage and a second order resistance-capacitance model
  • Extended Kalman Filter is used to eliminate the measurement and process noise
  • The algorithm also removes the need of prior knowledge of initial state of charge
  • Temperature variations that occur in a real world scenario are considered by obtaining model parameters from pulse discharge tests which are conducted at different standard temperatures and current ratings
  • The developed algorithm is tested under a variety of standard drive cycles and optimized for maximum efficiency
